
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `hp-colorcal` baraye kalibr kardan rang-haye chapgar-haye rangie HP estefade mishavad. In kar be shoma komak mikonad ta rang-haye daghigh-tari dar chap dashte bashid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `hp-colorcal -g`  --> 🎨  Ra'ngha ra bar asas-e dastoor-ol-amal grafik kalibr mikonad.
    🔹 `hp-colorcal -i`  --> 🖥  Ra'ngha ra bar asas-e dastoor-ol-amal tasvir kalibr mikonad.
    🔹 `hp-colorcal -q <level>` --> 🔎  Keyfiyat-e kalibrasieh ra ta'yin mikonad (az `draft` ta `best`).
    🔹 `hp-colorcal -p <printer>` --> 🖨  Printer-e mored nazar ra ta'yin mikonad agar bishtar az yek printer mojud bashad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ hp-colorcal -g -q best

    🔹 Kalibr kardan rangha baraye grafik ba keyfiyat-e balatarin.

    $ hp-colorcal -p DeskJet_3630 -i

    🔹 Kalibr kardan rangha baraye tasvir dar printer ba nam DeskJet_3630.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ hp-colorcal

    🔹 Agar printer pishfarz ta'yin shode bashad, dastoor-ol-amal kalibrasieh pishfarz ejra mishavad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `hp-colorcal` command is used to calibrate the colors of HP color printers. This helps you achieve more accurate colors in your prints.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `hp-colorcal -g`  --> 🎨 Calibrate colors based on graphics workflow.
    🔹 `hp-colorcal -i`  --> 🖥 Calibrate colors based on imaging workflow.
    🔹 `hp-colorcal -q <level>` --> 🔎 Set the calibration quality level (from `draft` to `best`).
    🔹 `hp-colorcal -p <printer>` --> 🖨 Specify the printer to use if multiple printers are available.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ hp-colorcal -g -q best

    🔹 Calibrate colors for graphics with the best quality setting.

    $ hp-colorcal -p DeskJet_3630 -i

    🔹 Calibrate colors for imaging on the printer named DeskJet_3630.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ hp-colorcal

    🔹 If a default printer is already configured, the default calibration workflow will be executed.
